column2: In observance of the Holy Week, we will be closed on April 9 and April 10. We will be back on Monday, April 13.  May you all have a blessed Holy Week!

We remain committed to serving you. In light of the extension of the enhanced community quarantine, please take note of the following service channels. You may also check our other advisories by clicking this link: https://bit.ly/2x9IHHs. Stay safe!

In AXA, we are committed to promoting women empowerment in the workplace, with programs that help advance their health and wellbeing and those that support the needs of working mothers. In celebration of Women‚Äôs Month, we give back to the women in the communities in which we work with a free cervical screening activity for public school teachers in partnership with the Philippine Cancer Society, and a financial literacy session to benefit the female employees of DepEd Manila.... We also put the spotlight on some of the remarkable WoMen@AXA through an exhibit that recognizes their strength of character, dedication to their profession, and their passion and purpose.  In photo: Peachy and Zaida are exemplary examples of women of strength, character and integrity. Peachy is married, a mother of three and a breast cancer survivor. Zaida is a single, independent woman that loves her furbabies. Peachy is a training and development professional, and Zaida is a certified internal auditor. Both of them excel in their chosen fields and lead fulfilling lives with work-life harmony.
